overview: "The user initiated a request for a comprehensive review of a recently
  implemented sleep questionnaire application. The primary goal was to verify
  that the application's database, API endpoints, and overall functionality met
  the detailed acceptance criteria provided in a lengthy document. This document
  specified that the questionnaire should be an interactive, AI-enabled tool,
  taking about 15 minutes to complete, and generating a narrative report with
  links to external resources. It also outlined the collection of de-identified
  demographic data (year of birth, zipcode/county, sex) and the functional
  output: either sleep health guidance or probable diagnoses for a range of
  sleep disorders. The assistant approached this by systematically reviewing
  various parts of the codebase, including the questionnaire's structural
  definitions, validation logic, database schema, API endpoints for submitting
  responses, generating CSV exports, and creating PDF reports. Additionally, the
  review covered the front-end components for the questionnaire form, the admin
  dashboard for data access, and the authentication mechanisms. The detailed
  review aimed to ensure all specified sections, branching logic, and reporting
  requirements were addressed in the current implementation."
